      "id": "mtg-gap-001",
      "question": "What is the difference between a HELOC and a cash-out refinance?",
      "answer": "A HELOC is a separate revolving line secured by your home, while a cash-out refinance replaces your existing first mortgage with a new, larger mortgage and gives you the difference in cash. Which one is better depends on your current rate, equity, goals, and whether you want one payment or a separate line of credit.",
      "content": "Primary question: What is the difference between a HELOC and a cash-out refinance?\nBorrower asks: What is the difference between a HELOC and a cash-out refinance?\nSearch phrases: What is the difference between a HELOC and a cash-out refinance? | what is the difference between a heloc and a cash-out refinance\nKeywords: cash out; equity; heloc; refinance\nDirect answer: A HELOC is a separate revolving line secured by your home, while a cash-out refinance replaces your existing first mortgage with a new, larger mortgage and gives you the difference in cash. Which one is better depends on your current rate, equity, goals, and whether you want one payment or a separate line of credit.\nExpanded answer: A HELOC is a separate revolving line secured by your home, while a cash-out refinance replaces your existing first mortgage with a new, larger mortgage and gives you the difference in cash. Which one is better depends on your current rate, equity, goals, and whether you want one payment or a separate line of credit.\nGuidance note: General mortgage guidance. Exact eligibility, limits, pricing, and overlays vary by program and lender.",
