      "id": "mtg-gap-003",
      "question": "What is a mortgage recast?",
      "answer": "A mortgage recast is when the servicer recalculates your monthly principal-and-interest payment after you make a large lump-sum principal payment, but the original loan usually stays in place. It is different from a refinance because you are not replacing the old loan with a new one.",
      "content": "Primary question: What is a mortgage recast?\nBorrower asks: What is a mortgage recast?\nSearch phrases: What is a mortgage recast? | what is a home loan recast | what is a mortgage recast\nKeywords: payment; recast; servicing\nDirect answer: A mortgage recast is when the servicer recalculates your monthly principal-and-interest payment after you make a large lump-sum principal payment, but the original loan usually stays in place. It is different from a refinance because you are not replacing the old loan with a new one.\nExpanded answer: A mortgage recast is when the servicer recalculates your monthly principal-and-interest payment after you make a large lump-sum principal payment, but the original loan usually stays in place. It is different from a refinance because you are not replacing the old loan with a new one.\nGuidance note: General mortgage guidance. Exact eligibility, limits, pricing, and overlays vary by program and lender.",
