      "id": "mtg-gap-005",
      "question": "What is a 2-1 buydown mortgage?",
      "answer": "A 2-1 buydown is a temporary interest-rate buydown where the borrower’s payment is typically reduced for the first two years before moving to the full note rate. It can help with early payment shock, but the borrower still needs to qualify under the applicable underwriting rules.",
