      "question": "Can I assume someone else's mortgage?",
      "answer": "Sometimes. Some government-backed loans, especially certain FHA and VA loans, may be assumable if the lender or servicer approves the transfer and the buyer qualifies. Many conventional loans are not freely assumable because of due-on-sale restrictions.",
