      "id": "mtg-gap-019",
      "question": "What is a gift of equity?",
      "answer": "A gift of equity is when a seller, often a family member, sells a property to the buyer for less than market value and treats the difference as a gift. It can sometimes help with down payment or equity requirements if properly documented and allowed by the loan program.",
