      "question": "What is a bridge loan versus a HELOC?",
      "answer": "A bridge loan is usually a short-term loan designed to help with timing between buying and selling properties, while a HELOC is a revolving line secured by available home equity. The better fit depends on whether you need temporary purchase timing support or flexible access to equity.",
